humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: Based on the pathology report, there are no positive lymph nodes found in the 5 assessed lymph nodes (0/5 positive for metastasis). This corresponds to the new rule 11, which states that N0 can indicate that all assessed lymph nodes are negative for metastatic carcinoma. Therefore, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that 0 out of 5 lymph nodes were positive for metastasis (Regional 0/5). This means that there is no evidence of cancer in the regional lymph nodes, which corresponds to an N0 stage.
